Pople, J. Chem. Phys. 72, 650 (1980). Na - Ar: (12s,9p) -> [6s,5p] A.D. McLean and G.S. Chandler J. Chem. Phys. 72, 5639, (1980) K - Ca: (14s,11p,3d)-> [8s,7p,1d] J-P. Blaudeau, M. P. McGrath, L.A. Phys. 103, 6104 (1995). I : (15s,12p,6d)-> [10s,9p,4d] M.N. Glukhovtsev, A. Pross, M.P. McGrath and L. Radom, J. Chem. Phys. 103, 1878 (1995).
This basis has increased flexibility in the valence region relative to the 6-31G basis because it uses three functions to represent each valence AO. The original 6-311G set is extended to second row elements using the McLean Chandler basis sets.

This collection of basis functions, along with the corresponding set of polarization functions, was chosen to give the lowest possible energy for the atomic ground states in frozen core UMP2 calculations. All entries below which are labelled E(UMP2) are frozen core.
For Be all exponents were optimized for the 1s2 2s1 2p1 excited 2-P state. For helium exponents were taken from Gaussian-89 and have not been published.
